25. 1100 per-cut. A play on the proverbial expression, et oleum et operam perdere. The ‘professional‘ of the Palaestra does not in the country, as in a public palaestra in the town, spend all his time in attendance on others, and so reap no substantial benefit himself from all his training (oleum the 0111113 was an essential part of the training)‚ but turns it to advantage in snaring‚ fishing‚ hunting, 610. Such a villa as Faustinus’s would no doubt have a palaestra attached to it.
